		<profileDesc>
			<abstract>
				<p>A novel approach to combining clustering and feature selection is presented. It implements a wrapper strategy for feature selection, in the sense that the features are directly selected by optimizing the discrimina-tive power of the used partitioning algorithm. On the technical side, we present an efficient optimization algorithm with guaranteed local convergence property. The only free parameter of this method is selected by a resampling-based stability analysis. Experiments with real-world datasets demonstrate that our method is able to infer both meaningful partitions and meaningful subsets of features.</p>
			</abstract>
